# BoskePulse App

macOS menu bar application (`LSUIElement`). SwiftUI + AppKit presenters.

## Key files

| File | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `BoskePulseApp.swift` | `@main` — `MenuBarExtra` entry |
| `AppModel.swift` | ObservableObject hub — engine lifecycle, polling, notifications |
| `ProductionDashboardView.swift` / `ProductionDashboardViews.swift` | Dashboard layout and tiles |
| `SettingsView.swift` | Coolify / Hetzner / Telegram credential form |
| `KeychainService.swift` | Keychain CRUD for tokens |
| `MenuBarIconRenderer.swift` | Health-colored status icon |
| `*WindowPresenter.swift` | Compact, production, settings windows |

## Patterns

- Keep orchestration in `AppModel`; delegate domain logic to `BoskePulseCore`.
- Write snapshots via `SnapshotStore` after each successful poll.
- Reload widget timelines after snapshot writes.
- Use `TailscaleCLIReachability` for app-side Tailscale status.

## UI conventions

- Theme constants in `ProductionDashboardViews.swift` (`BoskeTheme`, `PulseTheme`).
- Copy helpers: `PulseClipboard.swift`, `ServerCopyFormatter.swift`.
- Do not embed API tokens or secrets in views or view models.

## Signing

Both **BoskePulse** and **BoskePulseWidget** need App Group `group.eu.canopystudio.boske.pulse`.
